26 across is not wrong. The “rule” of “singular with singular, plural with plural” is an oversimplification. Clue and answer have to agree in meaning, not in grammatical form. “Turnovers” is a statistical category, so it’s a STAT. It’s not more than one of them. 

And each turnover in a game isn’t a separate stat. It’s part of the same stat.

